---
import BaseLayout from '@/app/layouts/base-layout.astro';

import { Server, Code, Database, Brain, Cloud } from '@lucide/astro';

const title = 'About Me';
const description =
  "";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}>
  <main class='main mt-10'>
    <h1 class='post-title'>About Me</h1>
    <p class='intro-text'>
      Welcome to my digital lab! I'm a software developer who builds robust, scalable applications. My journey from Industrial Engineering and Data Science to Java development gives me a unique perspective: I don't just write codeâ€”I build solutions that solve core business problems.
    </p>
    <p class="intro-text">
      My goal is to translate complex operational needs into clean, efficient, and maintainable software.
    </p>
    <h2 class="post-title">
      My Journey: From Process to Code
    </h2>
    <p class="intro-text">
      My career began in Industrial Engineering, where I optimized supply chains and manufacturing processes using methodologies like Kaizen. I soon discovered that the biggest improvements came from better data and systems. This led me to teach myself SQL and web development, where I spent several years building high-impact reporting and BI solutions.
    </p>
    <p class="intro-text">
      Key Achievement: I managed a full-scale reporting system migration from a legacy ERP to SAP B1, rebuilding all company reports using SQL and Crystal Reports and migrating KPI systems from MSSQL to HanaSQL.
    </p>
    <h2 class="post-title">
      Deepening the Tech Stack
    </h2>
    <p class="intro-text">
      To build more sophisticated solutions, I pursued a Master's in Data Science, mastering Python, R, and machine learning. This academic rigor, combined with practical experience, allows me to understand the entire data lifecycle, from extraction and analysis to model deployment.
    </p>
    <p class="intro-text">
      Driven to move from analyzing systems to building them, I immersed myself in full-stack Java development.
    </p>
    <h2 class="post-title">My Technical Toolkit</h2>
<div class="toolkit-container">
  <div class="icon-row">
    <Server />
    <p class="intro-text"><strong>Back-End:</strong> Java, Spring Boot, Spring Security, REST APIs</p>
  </div>
  <div class="icon-row">
    <Code />
    <p class="intro-text"><strong>Front-End:</strong> React, JavaScript, HTML, CSS</p>
  </div>
  <div class="icon-row">
    <Database />
    <p class="intro-text"><strong>Databases:</strong> SQL (MSSQL, PostgreSQL, HanaSQL), Database Design</p>
  </div>
  <div class="icon-row">
    <Brain />
    <p class="intro-text"><strong>Data Science:</strong> Python (Pandas, Scikit-learn), R, Machine Learning, Tableau</p>
  </div>
  <div class="icon-row">
    <Cloud />
    <p class="intro-text"><strong>DevOps & Cloud:</strong> AWS, Docker, Git, CI/CD, Automated Testing</p>
  </div>
</div>
    <h2 class="post-title">
      What I'm Working On Now
    </h2>
    <p class="intro-text">
      I'm passionate about continuous learning and building practical tools. My current projects include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Developing a full-featured Warehouse Management System (WMS) using Spring Boot, integrating BI and forecasting.
      </li>
      <li>
        Implementing robust automated testing and CI/CD pipelines for my personal projects.
      </li>
      <li>
        Sharing my learnings on this blog.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="intro-text">
      Let's Build Something Great
    </p>
    <p class="intro-text">
      I am currently seeking a Java Developer role where I can leverage my unique blend of software engineering, data analysis, and process optimization skills. If you're looking for a developer who understands the business logic behind the code, let's connect.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .intro-text {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Tech Stack section */

  .toolkit-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .icon-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .icon-row svg {
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    margin-right: 0.75rem;
    color: #4a5568; /* A dark gray color */
    display: inline-flex; /* Ensures the SVG bahaves like an inline element */
  }
  .intro-text {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .post-title {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
